cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep learning approaches for inferring numerical coordinates for points of interest in an input image. This problem is closely related to computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new layer called DSNT, which is fully differentiable and exhibits good spatial generalization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. Additionally, the paper proposes a new technique that offers a better trade-off between inference speed and prediction accuracy compared to existing techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of inferring numerical coordinates for points of interest in an input image is also relevant to robotics, which suggests that the paper may belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper deals with deep learning approaches for image analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
